  "prompt": "What is the meaning of \"Are you game?\"",
  "response": "\"Are you game?\" means **\"Are you willing to participate in something, usually something risky, daring, or fun?\"** It's an invitation to join in on an activity, and it implies that the activity might be a little challenging or exciting.\n\nThink of it like asking:\n\n*   Are you up for it?\n*   Are you willing to try it?\n*   Do you want to play along?\n*   Are you brave enough?\n\nThe word \"game\" here isn't necessarily referring to a literal game, but rather a general activity or plan.\n\nFor example:\n\n*   \"I'm thinking of sneaking out tonight. Are you game?\" (implies sneaking out is a bit risky)\n*   \"I'm going to try that new spicy challenge at the restaurant. Are you game?\" (implies the challenge will be intense)\n*   \"We're thinking of going on a spontaneous road trip this weekend. Are you game?\" (implies the trip will be unplanned and adventurous)\n",
